Start
- write out 'Starting Async Goal Call tests...'

/ Test 1: Call goal without waiting - main execution should continue immediately
- set %startTime% to %Now%
- call !SlowGoal, dont wait
- set %afterCallTime% to %Now%
/ The call should return immediately, not wait for SlowGoal to complete
- write out 'Test 1: Main thread continued after async call'

/ Test 2: Call goal with waiting (default behavior)
- set %beforeWait% to %Now%
- call !QuickGoal
- set %afterWait% to %Now%
- write out 'Test 2 passed: Synchronous call waited for completion'

/ Give async goal time to complete
- wait for 200 ms

/ Test 3: Verify async goal did run (it should have written to a file)
- read file 'async_marker.txt' into %asyncContent%
    on error call !HandleMissingFile
- if %asyncContent% is not empty then
    - [assert] %asyncContent% contains 'async_completed'
        on error call !AssertFailed
    - write out 'Test 3 passed: Async goal completed in background'
- delete file 'async_marker.txt'
    on error continue to next step

- write out 'All Async Goal Call tests passed!'

SlowGoal
/ This goal runs asynchronously - write a marker file to prove it ran
- wait for 100 ms
- write 'async_completed' to file 'async_marker.txt'

QuickGoal
- set %dummy% to 'done'

HandleMissingFile
- write out 'Note: Async marker file not found (async goal may not have completed yet)'

AssertFailed
- write out 'FAILED: Assertion error occurred'
- write out 'Error: %!error.Message%'
